radiographic_examinations.findings: Lung bases are clear. No pleural effusion. Normal visualized portions of the heart. Imaged portions of the liver enhance homogeneously with no focal hepatic lesions. Normal gallbladder, portal vein patent, normal adrenal glands, pancreas and spleen. Kidneys enhance symmetrically without hydronephrosis or renal masses. Stomach contains ingested material mixed with contrast. Dilated appendix measuring up to 1.6 cm with multiple appendicoliths and surrounding free fluid layering within the pelvis. No definite extraluminal air or lymph node enlargement.
